"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-olympic-flame-lighting-olympia-torch-relay-paris-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Olympic torch relay for the Paris Games began Tuesday at the ancient Olympic site of Olympia, Greece, starting a trek for the Olympic Flame that will last through the July 26 Opening Ceremony.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4, \"end\": 17, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.67160604718982e-29, \"text\": \"Olympic torch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\"}, {\"begin\": 89, \"end\": 104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympia, Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 89, \"end\": 104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympia, Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cloudy skies prevented the traditional lighting, when an actress dressed as an ancient Greek priestess uses the sun to ignite a silver torch.\", \"from\": 198, \"to\": 339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 277, \"end\": 290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9952081693042117, \"rank\": 0.0033735781836961754, \"text\": \"ancient Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, a backup flame was used that had been lit on the same spot Monday, during the final rehearsal.\", \"from\": 341, \"to\": 444, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Normally, the foremost of a group of priestesses in long, pleated dresses offers a prayer to the ancient Greek sun god, Apollo.\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 543, \"end\": 556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9952081693042117, \"rank\": 0.0033735781836961754, \"text\": \"ancient Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 566, \"end\": 572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\", \"score\": 0.9999999982783265, \"rank\": 1.7216187506107378e-09, \"text\": \"Apollo\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She then dips the fuel-filled torch into a parabolic mirror which focuses the sun's rays on it, and fire spurts forth.\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tokyo Olympic rowing gold medalist Stefanos Ntouskos of Greece was the first torchbearer.\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 783, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 694, \"end\": 699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9585523893954844, \"rank\": 0.043204604914793, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 729, \"end\": 746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stefanos Ntouskos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\"}, {\"begin\": 750, \"end\": 756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9849655812359053, \"rank\": 0.015263661967703058, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He handed off to retired French swimmer Laure Manaudou, a three-time medalist at the 2004 Athens Games.\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 887, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 824, \"end\": 838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Manaudou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laure Manaudou\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Manaudou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Manaudou\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The flame will spend 11 days in Greece, including visiting Athens and the Panathenaic Stadium, which hosted events at the first modern Olympics in 1896.\", \"from\": 889, \"to\": 1041, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 921, \"end\": 927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9849655812359053, \"rank\": 0.015263661967703058, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 948, \"end\": 954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9998892066460876, \"rank\": 0.000110805630552755, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The flame will then cross the Mediterranean Sea aboard the Belem, a three-masted ship, \\\"reminiscent of a true Homeric epic,\\\" according to Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1192, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1102, \"end\": 1107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\", \"score\": 0.9903282791598326, \"rank\": 0.00799898425596817, \"text\": \"Belem\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\"}, {\"begin\": 1153, \"end\": 1165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Homer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Homeric epic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Homer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Homer\"}, {\"begin\": 1181, \"end\": 1191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9135353517716917e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will arrive at the Old Port of Marseille, welcomed by an armada of boats, for the French leg of the relay from May 8 through July 26.\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1228, \"end\": 1237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9999999999749889, \"rank\": 2.509440292154292e-11, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French leg includes a June 8-17 portion visiting overseas territories French Guiana, Reunion, French Polynesia, Guadeloupe and Martinique.\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1474, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1406, \"end\": 1419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Guiana\", \"score\": 0.9999999999984084, \"rank\": 9.15290685992169e-13, \"text\": \"French Guiana\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Guiana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Guiana\"}, {\"begin\": 1406, \"end\": 1419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Guiana\", \"score\": 0.9999999999984084, \"rank\": 9.15290685992169e-13, \"text\": \"French Guiana\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Guiana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Guiana\"}, {\"begin\": 1421, \"end\": 1428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reunion_Records\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.071434731413657e-14, \"text\": \"Reunion\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reunion_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reunion_Records\"}, {\"begin\": 1437, \"end\": 1446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9946221911808798, \"rank\": 0.005406886018100981, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In France, the flame will visit more than 400 cities and towns across 64 territories.\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1479, \"end\": 1485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999996781648923, \"rank\": 1.653515897035155e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will go by D-Day beaches, Mont Saint-Michel, the Palace of Versailles, Cannes, Roland Garros and more famous vineyards and museums.\", \"from\": 1562, \"to\": 1696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1636, \"end\": 1642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cannes\", \"score\": 0.9999885918364718, \"rank\": 1.1374545310404923e-05, \"text\": \"Cannes\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cannes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cannes\"}, {\"begin\": 1644, \"end\": 1657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"score\": 0.9920756779366529, \"rank\": 0.007987618335275937, \"text\": \"Roland Garros\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 10,000 individual torchbearers will run about 200 meters each, plus 3,000 torchbearers participating in team relays.\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1817, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Associated Press contributed to this report.\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1867, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1823, \"end\": 1839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999999947447122, \"rank\": 4.7545318186588685e-09, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\ud83d\\udd25 The Olympic flame for#Paris2024is lit!#Paris2024|@Paris2024pic.twitter.com/1odw4ga9G0  From one Olympic champion to another!\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 1995, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stefanos Ntouskos \\ud83c\\uddec\\ud83c\\uddf7 hands the flame to Laure Manaudou \\ud83c\\uddeb\\ud83c\\uddf7, an Olympic champion swimmer.Traditionally, a Greek athlete is the first torchbearer, followed by a representative from the host nation.#Paris2024|@Paris2024pic.twitter.com/RnpQoGt8cC    A Division ofNBCUniversal.\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1997, \"end\": 2014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stefanos Ntouskos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\"}, {\"begin\": 2039, \"end\": 2053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Manaudou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laure Manaudou\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Manaudou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laure_Manaudou\"}, {\"begin\": 2246, \"